    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - DOOR GLASS REAR RUN CHANNEL AND CHANNEL SEAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DOOR GLASS REAR RUN CHANNEL AND CHANNEL SEAL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The door glass rear run channel seal (weather stripping) is molded for a compression fit in window
                frame as well as in glass rear run channel. No clips are required to retain it. Channel and seal are
                removed and installed together.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600732">Figure 32</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600732" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600732" filename="../figg16/G1600732.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Door Glass Rear Run Channel and Channel Seal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. REAR RUN CHANNEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHANNEL SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DOOR WINDOW FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ACCESS OPENING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WINDOW REGULATOR HANDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cab door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_25.xml" xrefid="x1600708">CAB DOOR GLASS, Remove</hotlnk>. Glass may be
                    left in bottom of door or removed through access opening as desired.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pry out channel seal (Item 2) from door window frame (Item 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Since rear run channel (Item 1) is already loosened as outlined in Step 1 above, remove
                    rear run channel and seal (Items 1 and 2) through door access opening (Item 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Obtain replacement rear run channel seal (Item 2) and insert lower end in rear run
                    channel (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place rear run channel and seal assembly inside door and press upper end of seal into
                    window frame (Item 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install cab door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_25.xml" xrefid="x1600709">CAB DOOR GLASS, Install</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
